                                <p>Nastaʻlīq; copied in black ink, with headings in red. </p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>Includes some marginal comments. </p>
                            <p><locus>f. 1r</locus> includes a scrubbed out seal and several damaged
                                inscriptions, one dated 1139 (1726/27). </p>
                            <p>Occasional marginal comments in English in what appears to be
                                    <persName role="fmo">Robinson</persName>'s hand.</p>
                            <p>Pastedown containing Robinson's signature 'Revd. T. Robinson' and
                                bookplate 'Collegii Sti. Augustini apud Cantuarienses Liber'. Marked
                                'Librarian's room 31. </p>
                            <p>Flyleaf with label: "Presented to
                                St. Augustine's College Library by the Rev. Thomas Robinson, D.D.,
                                late Archdeacon of Madras." </p>
                        </additions>
